                    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-4">The "age of US-led AI hegemony" is facing its strongest challenge yet. The strategic open-sourcing by Chinese tech giants is fundamentally altering the competitive landscape, pushing Western proprietary firms to re-evaluate their models and pricing.</p>
                    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">The future "soul of tomorrow's intelligence infrastructure" is likely to be a complex interplay of open and closed systems, where cost, accessibility, trust, and geopolitical alignment will define market leadership and global influence.</p>
